      ],
      "source": "https://www.greatermilfordhistorical.org/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town was carved from Unadilla in 1796 as “Suffrage” before adopting the name Milford in 1800.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The first settler arrived around 1770, but the community really took off after the Revolutionary War.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Susquehanna River runs south through Milford, joined by Cherry Valley Creek.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "New York State Route 166 meets NY‑28 in Milford village, while NY‑7 also crosses NY‑28 in the south.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
